Last updated at 12:01AM, March 29 2012
Saleh Mutawa was a poor man and he died a poor man’s death.
A secondhand clothes trader from a small Sunni town in northern Syria, the soldiers who killed him on Monday did so casually, shooting him in the head as he approached their checkpoint on the outskirts of Sarmin. They left him dead at the wheel of his van, blood from his face running through his cheap striped jersey to drip on the flip-flops that remained on his feet.
